<%# Phase 32 follow-up (2026-05-16). Voyage section of the Stack pane,
    extracted so the `ReindexAllJob` can broadcast a Turbo Stream
    replace targeted at the wrapping `<div id="voyage_section">`
    without re-rendering the entire stack pane.

    Two states, gated entirely on `AppSetting.reindex_running?`:

      * idle    — the `[reindex]` destructive bracketed link wired to
                  the `reindex_meilisearch_modal` confirm modal
                  (the modal itself is rendered once at page level in
                  `_stack_pane.html.erb`, OUTSIDE this broadcast
                  target — see the CSRF note below).
      * running — the `dot-loader` `=/-` compound loading indicator
                  (`.dot-loader` in `tailwind/application.css`, also
                  used by `syncs/progress.html.erb`) + a small
                  "reindexing... started ~Xs ago" line driven by
                  the existing `compact_time_ago` helper.

    The wrapping id matches `target: "voyage_section"` in
    `ReindexAllJob#broadcast_voyage_section`. The view reads the
    flag fresh every render so the post-redirect page load already
    shows the running state without waiting for the broadcast.

    CSRF / broadcast note. The `ConfirmModalComponent` form must NOT
    live inside this partial. `Turbo::StreamsChannel.broadcast_replace_to`
    renders the partial in a JOB context with no `request` and no
    `session`, so `form_with` would bake a hidden `authenticity_token`
    that is unbound to any user's session — the next submit hits
    `ActionController::InvalidAuthenticityToken`. The modal is
    mounted once in `_stack_pane.html.erb`, generated in a real
    request context, with a CSRF token bound to the current
    session. The broadcast only swaps the visual state of the
    trigger affordance. %>
<%# 2026-05-18 (DR) — Voyage stats line added between the heading and
    the action row. `Voyage::Stats.call` is a sub-millisecond aggregate
    read (count + max per target), safe to call on every settings
    render. Bundle keys come back nil when the `summary_embedding`
    column is not yet on the bundles table — the view degrades to "—"
    on those without raising. %>
<%# 2026-05-18 (table polish) — replaced the single-line `<p>` summary
    with a 2-column `metric / value` table using the shared
    `.stack-table` class (defined in `tailwind/application.css`). The
    class gives Voyage the SAME edges, header tint, zebra rows, and
    cell padding as the Postgres / Meilisearch / assets / notes tables
    in `_stack_pane.html.erb` — even though Voyage's data is
    heterogeneous (counts, bytes, time-ago strings) rather than a
    repeating row shape, the operator sees a consistent slab across
    every pane.

    Row visibility:
      * games row             — always shown
      * bundles row           — only when `total_bundles_count > 0`
                                (mirrors the original guard; the
                                `bundles.summary_embedding` column is
                                absent on fresh installs and
                                `Voyage::Stats#bundle_counts` returns
                                nil → 0 in that case)
      * model row             — always shown
      * last indexed row      — only when `last_indexed_at` is set
      * storage row           — only when `storage_kb` is non-nil
      * last 24h row          — only when count > 0

    Polling targets (`data-stack-stats-live-target`) are preserved on
    every numeric/text cell so the existing `stack_stats_live`
    controller can patch values in place every ~3 s without any DOM
    structure change. %>
<% voyage_stats = Voyage::Stats.call %>
<div id="voyage_section">
  <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
    <span><strong>Voyage AI</strong></span>
    <% if AppSetting.voyage_configured? %>
      <span style="color: var(--color-success);">▲ configured</span>
    <% else %>
      <span class="text-danger">▽ not configured</span>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
    <table class="stack-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>metric</th>
          <th class="num">value</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>games embedded</td>
          <td class="num">
            <span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyageEmbedded"><%= number_with_delimiter(voyage_stats[:embedded_games_count].to_i) %></span>
            / <span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyageTotal"><%= number_with_delimiter(voyage_stats[:total_games_count].to_i) %></span>
            (<span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyagePct"><%= voyage_stats[:coverage_pct] %></span>%)
          </td>
        </tr>
        <% if voyage_stats[:total_bundles_count].to_i > 0 %>
          <tr>
            <td>bundles embedded</td>
            <td class="num">
              <span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyageBundlesEmbedded"><%= number_with_delimiter(voyage_stats[:embedded_bundles_count].to_i) %></span>
              / <span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyageBundlesTotal"><%= number_with_delimiter(voyage_stats[:total_bundles_count].to_i) %></span>
            </td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
        <tr>
          <td>model</td>
          <td class="num"><%= voyage_stats[:model] %></td>
        </tr>
        <% if voyage_stats[:last_indexed_at] %>
          <tr>
            <td>last indexed</td>
            <td class="num">
              <span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyageLast"><%= compact_time_ago(voyage_stats[:last_indexed_at]) %></span>
            </td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
        <% if voyage_stats[:storage_kb] %>
          <tr>
            <td>storage</td>
            <td class="num">
              <span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyageStorage"><%= number_with_delimiter(voyage_stats[:storage_kb].to_i) %></span> KB
            </td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
        <% if voyage_stats[:embeddings_last_24h].to_i > 0 %>
          <tr>
            <td>last 24h</td>
            <td class="num">
              <span data-stack-stats-live-target="voyage24h"><%= number_with_delimiter(voyage_stats[:embeddings_last_24h].to_i) %></span> embeddings
            </td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <% if AppSetting.reindex_running? %>
    <%# Running state. Reuses the `.dot-loader` `=/- ` indicator
        from the Sync progress page (definition in
        `app/assets/tailwind/application.css`). The randomized
        `--loader-delay` matches the convention in
        `syncs/progress.html.erb` so the cell does not feel locked
        to a single phase. %>
    <div class="dot-list" style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <span class="dot-loader" style="--loader-delay: -0.25s"></span>
      <span class="text-muted" style="margin-left: 6px;">
        reindexing... started <%= compact_time_ago(AppSetting.reindex_started_at) %>
      </span>
    </div>
  <% else %>
    <div class="dot-list" style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(
        label: "reindex",
        href: "#",
        destructive: true,
        data: {
          controller: "modal-trigger",
          action: "click->modal-trigger#open",
          modal_trigger_target_id_value: "reindex_meilisearch_modal"
        }
      )) %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
